$ System.Activator (class)

`System.Activator` allows to dynamically create types, given an instance of → Microsoft/dot-net/namespaces-classes/System/Type[`System.Type`].

{ Example

  The following simple → development/languages/C-Sharp[C#] example tries to demonstrate how `Activator` might be used.

  gh|.NET-API|/System/Activator/intro.cs||

  When executed, this sample prints
code {
num = 42, txt = Hello World
num = 99, txt = Foo bar baz
code }

}
